                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301028-234-off1310 t18301028-234-crimeloc1312"></join>. On the 27th of April Williams came and brought this letter - he said he came from Mr. Horne, to borrow three sovereigns; I asked him if he would wait, as my husband was out - he was there three quarters of an hour, and I asked him a great many questions; at last, in consequence of the letter, and believing he came from Mr. Horne, I gave him the three sovereigns; I know nothing of Wood - this is the letter - he asked if there was any work to go back, and I gave him the two rings.</p>
